t: Unto*p thee lift I up mine eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens.

Behold,*p as the eyes of servants look unto the hand of their masters, and as the eyes of a maiden unto the hand of her mistress; so our eyes wait upon the Lord*s our God, until that he have mercy upon us.
Have*p mercy upon us, O Lord,*s have mercy upon us: for we are exceedingly filled with contempt.
Our*p soul is exceedingly filled with the scorning of those that are at ease, and with the contempt of the proud.
